0.1.1.name: wordpress/collapsing-pages
0.1.1.description:
This is a very simple plugin that uses Javascript to form a collapsable set of links in the sidebar for the pages. Every page corresponding to a given parent page will be expanded.

It is largely based off of my Collapsing Pages and Collapsing Archives plugins.

= What's new?=

  • 0.6.1 (2010.06.21)

    • Removed extraneous debugging info (subpagecount=)

  • 0.6 (2010.06.18)

    • Fixed html validation bug when linkToPage is false (thanks to levente.csabai)
    • fixed html parsing error in widget (thanks to vbonline)'
